---
import RootLayout from '../components/RootLayout.astro'
import GoToAppButton from '../components/GoToAppButton.astro';
---
<style>
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
  }

  .center {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .title-section {
    margin-top: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 100px;
  }

  .section {
    margin-top: 50px;
  }

  img.preview {
    max-width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 1px 1px 7px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
</style>
<RootLayout title="Feynote">
  <div class="center">
    <div class="title-section">
      <h1>Welcome to FeyNote!</h1>

      A free note-taking app for world-builders and tabletop RPG players.<br />

      Embed statblocks and spells, encourage collaborative session notes, and organize your world by placing pins on a map.

      <br />
      <br />

      <GoToAppButton />
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Advanced Editor</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-artifact-20240924.jpg" alt="FeyNote Artifact Editor" />

      FeyNote's editor is very powerful. We've added the ability to embed monsters, spells, and items directly into your notes.<br />
      Edit offline when away from an internet connection, and your content will sync up when you come back online (yes, even though it's a website!).
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Sharing and Collaboration</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-sharing-20240924.jpg" alt="FeyNote Sharing Options" />

      FeyNote is built with sharing in mind from the ground up. Live collaborate or share read-only copies with players, the choice is yours!
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>References and Linked Content</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-references-20240924.jpg" alt="FeyNote Calendar" />

      You can quickly and easily reference related content between your artifacts, reducing duplication and keeping your references up to date when the content changes. You can choose how to organize your content, whether that be in a graph-like structure or in a nested tree-like structure.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Fantasy Calendars</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-calendar-20240924.jpg" alt="FeyNote Calendar" />

      FeyNote's calendar functionality is extremely flexible. You can specify any fantasy calendar layout you might imagine.<br />
      Customize the number of months in a year, the number of days in each month, and the names of everything!
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Graph Visualization</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-graph-20240924.jpg" alt="FeyNote Graph Visualizer" />

      Visualize the content within your collection in a graph view. Particularly useful for large collections with lots of relationships, the graph view gives you a browsable view of everything in your collection.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Assistant and Content Scraping</h2>
      <img class="preview" src="https://static.feynote.com/screenshots/feynote-chatbot-20250716.jpg" alt="FeyNote AI Thread" />

      Don't worry, we've only included AI because it's genuinely helpful for some things such as formatting/creating custom monster blocks and items, as well as scraping content from the web!
    </div>
  </div>
</RootLayout>
